          <template v-if="instructionsModalType == 'free_local_listings'">
            <h2>Free Local Listings Program</h2>
            <p>Google Merchant Center's Free Local Listings program allows retailers to showcase their in-store products on Google for free. This initiative helps businesses increase their visibility to local shoppers by displaying their products on Google Search and Google Maps, making it easier for consumers to discover and consider their offerings when searching for items nearby. It's a powerful tool for brick-and-mortar stores aiming to drive more foot traffic and connect with their local community online.</p>
            <h4>Instructions</h4>
            <p>To Enroll in the Free Local Listings program, you must have:</p>
            <ul>    
              <li><strong>Verify Your Business Information:</strong> <br> Once you have been granted access to GMC via your email, ensure that your GMC account's business information is set up correctly. If anything is missing or requires adjustment, you can update this information from within the Business Information section of your GMC account.</li>
              <li><strong>Google Business Profile Setup:</strong> <br> Create and verify your business's Google Business Profile, ensuring accurate information about your physical store locations. Enter your store(s) code in the respective fields here.</li>
              <li><strong>Free Local Listings Enrollment:</strong> <br> Enroll in the Free Local Listings program within the GMC account to avail of its benefits for showcasing your products in local searches.</li>              
              <li><strong>Inventory Verification:</strong> <br> Within your GMC account, navigate to the Manage Programs and go to Free Local Listings settings. Look for the "Inventory verification" section and follow the on-screen instructions. This might involve a verification call or visit to confirm your stock levels.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>By completing these steps, your business will be eligible to appear in local searches on Google, potentially with real-time product availability for customers.</p>
          </template>  
          
          <template v-if="instructionsModalType == 'free_listings'">
            <h2>Free Listings Program</h2>
            <p>Google Merchant Center Free Listings program offers businesses the opportunity to display their products on Google Shopping for free. This initiative broadens the visibility of merchants' products beyond paid advertisements, allowing them to appear in relevant search results across Google Search and the Shopping tab. It's designed to help businesses of all sizes connect with more customers by making their products easily discoverable online, enhancing both reach and engagement without additional advertising costs.</p>
            <h4>Instructions</h4>
            <p>To enroll in the Free Listings program, follow these steps:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Verify Your Business Information:</strong> <br> Ensure that your GMC account's business information is accurately set up. If any details are missing or require adjustments, you can update them from within the Business Information section of your GMC account.</li>
              <li><strong>Free Listings Enrollment:</strong> <br> Enroll in the Free Listings program within your GMC account to benefit from enhanced visibility for your products across Google's various platforms.</li>
              <li><strong>Shipping Settings Configuration:</strong> <br> Ensure that your shipping settings are configured correctly within your ecommerce website. Additionally, verify these settings within your GMC account. Although our backend system automatically synchronizes shipping services configured in your ecommerce site with your GMC account, we recommend verifying the settings on GMC. If you are utilizing advanced shipping services and shipping carriers, make sure to create the same settings within the GMC shipping settings section.</li>
              <li><strong>Policy Pages Setup:</strong> <br> Set up policy pages such as return, exchange, and refund policies. Below, we provide a section for setting up these pages along with boilerplate templates. We encourage you to carefully review and customize these templates according to your business needs and policies.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>By completing these steps, your business will gain increased exposure to potential customers through Google's extensive network, helping drive traffic and sales to your online store.</p>
          </template>  

          <div slot="modal-footer">
            <b-button class="mr-0" @click="$refs.instructionsModal.hide()">Close</b-button>
